.TH Man Page : hsh

.SH NAME
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The "hsh" program is a simplified version of a shell with a simpler reprogramming approach.

.SH USAGE
To use this program in interactive mode, run "./hsh". A prompt ("$") will be presented, allowing you to input commands.

.PP
- To execute a command, type the following and press Enter.
.PP
$ [COMMAND] [ARGUMENT(S)]
.PP
- To exit the shell, type the following and press Enter.
.PP
$ exit
.PP
- To display environment variables, type the following and press Enter.
.PP
$ env
.PP
To use this program in non-interactive mode, input the following and press Enter:
.PP
echo "[COMMAND] [ARGUMENT(S)]" | ./hsh

.SH EXAMPLES
In interactive mode:
.PP
$ ls
.PP
AUTHORS README.md env.c loop.c shell.h man_1_simple_shell path_strtok.c strtok.c wait.c

.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.PP
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.PP
